    "body": "## Problem\n\nNo unified interface for logging.\n\nRequirements:\n\n- Near-zero-cost for disabled log levels. For example, `log.debug(...)` should be skipped if log-level is \"info\".\n- Formatting: plugins can override formatting\n- Filtering: ??\n- Sinks: plugins can send logs to other \"sinks\" (besides `$NVIM_LOG_FILE`)\n- RPC clients can use it\n- Logging can be enabled per-channel (see [Vim ch_logfile](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/9010)).\n\n## Expected behavior\n\nIntroduce `vim.log`. Start simple, keep the door open for advanced features in the future.\n\n### Performance:\n- Avoid table arguments (similar to `vim.validate()`) to avoid unnecessary overhead.\n- Provide printf-like formatting so that callers do NOT perform the formatting themselves. `log.debug(..., a, b, c)` is \"near-zero-cost\", whereas `log.debug(..., my_format(a, b, c))` expensive.\n- RPC calls to `nvim_log` are ignored if logging is disabled for that channel.\n\n### Interface:\n\n- `vim.log`\n- `nvim_log` calls `vim.log`\n- Global log-level is controlled by the 'verbose' option. (May need to adjust some internal `if p_verbose` checks)\n- `Log` event ([\"deferred autocmd\" #35366](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/35366), can be [received on channels](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/34399)).\n    - This is the mechanism for adding \"sinks\". Passive event, not for \"control\".\n    - `pattern` = log-level\n\nDetails:\n\n```\nvim.log.log(level: string, ns: string, topic: string, fmt: fun(),\n  msg: string, <varargs...>)\nvim.log.error()\nvim.log.warn()\nvim.log.info()\nvim.log.debug()\n```\n\n### Extensibility:\n\nOpen question: Need to choose between one of these approaches:\n\n```lua\nlocal log = function()\n  return vim.log.log(...)\nend\n```\n\nor this:\n\n```lua\nlocal log = vim.log.Log(...)\n```\n\nRelated:\n- #7062\n- #9010\n- #12503",
